s. Hence, consideration is given to the incorporation of multidimensional aspects of learning and experience in Holocaust education in order to enhance students' understanding on cognitive, emotional and moral levels. This book will help Holocaust educators and curriculum developers to design Holocaust education programs and attune them to the nature and the needs of the current generation. It is intended to prepare educators to initiate and lead programs and encounters designed to teach today’s youth about the Holocaust from multiple perspectives.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xInfluence. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh1 aBrutin, Batya, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCassuto, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidovitch, Nitza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavidovitch, Nitza, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDorot, Ruth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGawron, Edyta, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGerstenfeld, Manfred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGil, Zvi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaber, Lily, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKaźmierczak, Marek, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKnobler, Haim Y., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrgad, Zvi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoen, Dan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoen, Dan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aUr-Leurer, Osnat, econtribu